The $ 5\times 5$ grid shown contains a collection of squares with sizes from $ 1\times 1$ to $ 5\times 5$. How many of these squares contain the black center square?\\

\begin{asy}
import olympiad;
import cse5;
defaultpen(white);
size(100);
unitsize(6mm);
defaultpen(linewidth(.8pt));

for(int i=0; i<=5; ++i)
{
draw((0,i)--(5,i));
draw((i,0)--(i,5));
}
fill((2,2)--(2,3)--(3,3)--(3,2)--cycle);
\end{asy}
\\
$ \textbf{(A)}\ 12\qquad
\textbf{(B)}\ 15\qquad
\textbf{(C)}\ 17\qquad
\textbf{(D)}\ 19\qquad
\textbf{(E)}\ 20$
